==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Judaizer
<hw>Ju"da*i`zer</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>One who conforms
to or inculcates Judaism;</def> <specif>specifically,</specif>
<pluf>pl.</pluf> <fld>(Ch. Hist.)</fld>, <def>those Jews who accepted
Christianity but still adhered to the law of Moses and worshiped in the
temple at Jerusalem.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Judaizers</ent>⟦br⟧
